			<link href="http://localhost:4000/ghp/design/breadcrumb/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Breadcrumbs" />
			<updated>2014-07-10T00:00:00+08:00</updated>

			
				
				<author>
					
						<name>Bndy</name>
					
					
						<email>zb@bndy.net</email>
					
					
						<uri>http://bndy.net</uri>
					
				</author>
			
			<summary>If you need them, &lt;em&gt;Feeling Responsive&lt;/em&gt; offers you a breadcrumb navigation. You can easily turn it on/off via frontmatter.</summary>
			<content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/ghp/design/breadcrumb/">&lt;!--more--&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;alert-box alert &quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;WARNING: If you use breadcrumbs be aware, that if you use categories, you need pages for those categories. If not, the link in the breadcrumb won’t work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;front-matter-code&quot;&gt;Front Matter Code&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;breadcrumb: true
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</content>

			
